A [[en/Community/Patches/Patches]] that helps you managing trains by reporting vehicle as '''lost''' if the station it is currently heading to has not been reached in this amount of time.

== Description ==

When a train has not arrived at station for a set amount of time, the message will appear.
Often trains get lost because
-of the traffic jam on a junction
-a signal is placed at the wrong side
-[[en/Manual/Disasters|piece of track has been destroyed]]
-station is not connected to railway track with train on

You can click on the message to center main screen over the train in order to fix the problem

<center>[[File:en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Losttrain.png|center|frame|Train 1 has not arrived at station for a long time]]</center>
== Use ==
This feature is set to 180 days by default. You can set peroid of time needed for warning message to pop up or disable this feature through the [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Configuring patches/Vehicles|configure patches -> vehicles]] window or use the following syntax in [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Openttd.cfg]]:

<pre>
[patches]
lost_train_days = 180
</pre>